summary:
The Security Council, 
Recalling resolution 2664 (2022) and previous resolutions on the ISIL (Da’esh) and Al-Qaida sanctions regime, 
Reaffirming previous determinations on threats to international peace and security, 
Acting under Chapter VII of the Charter, 
1. Decides to continue provisions introduced by paragraph 1 of resolution 2664 (2022) for the 1267/1989/2253 ISIL (Da’esh) and Al-Qaida sanctions regime; 
2. Recalls the 1267/1989/2253 Sanctions Committee's role in monitoring implementation and calls on States to cooperate with the Committee and its Analytical Support and Sanctions Monitoring Team; 
3. Affirms the importance of Council consideration of information on implementation, including possible violations, and reported cases of abuse of non-profit organizations; 
4. Reiterates that providers should use reasonable efforts to eliminate or minimize benefits accruing to sanctioned individuals or entities; 
5. Decides to remain seized of this matter
